omance and Spanish Studies, gives a detailed description of American Spanish both regionally and historically, contrasting it with the European norm. It contains an updated bibliography and a number of useful exercises.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aLanguages in contactzAmerica. 0aSpanish languagexDialectszAmerica. 4aAmerika. 4aSpanisch. 4aVarietätenlinguistik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aAmerica.  aLanguage Variation.  aSpanish.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2014z9783110370270oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103740940 cprintz978311034038940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311034039640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110340396423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110340396/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014  aZDB-23-DSPb2014